# ── Vercel deployment ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional: override the default Chromium binary URL used by the PDF function.
# The binary is downloaded to /tmp on cold start. Hosting on your own CDN
# (Cloudflare R2, S3) is faster than the GitHub default.
#
# CHROMIUM_BINARY_URL=https://github.com/Sparticuz/chromium/releases/download/v133.0.0/chromium-v133.0.0-pack.tar
#
# ── Local development ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Point to your system Chrome so PDF works locally without downloading a binary:
#
# Mac:
# PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH=/Applications/Google Chrome.app/Contents/MacOS/Google Chrome
#
# Linux:
# PUPPETEER_EXECUTABLE_PATH=/usr/bin/google-chrome
#
# Translation uses Google Translate's free public endpoint — no API key,
# no signup. If you want to switch to a paid provider later (Anthropic,
# OpenAI, DeepL) for higher-quality business Japanese, swap the
# implementation in src/app/api/translate/route.ts.
